HEADWORD: Topiary
<hw>Top"i*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>topiarius</ets> belonging to ornamental gardening, fr.
<ets>topia</ets> (sc. <ets>opera</ets>) ornamental gardening, fr. Gr.
<?/ a place.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to ornamental gardening;
produced by cutting, trimming, etc.; topiarian.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Topiary work</b></col>, <cd>arbors, shrubbery, hedges, or
the like, cut and trimmed into fanciful forms, as of animals, buildings,
etc.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

